properties.descriptio: Thousands of straw-coloured fruit bats (Eidolon helvum) migrate from Chapwani Private Island to the mainland Zanzibar for their night time feast, returning to the save haven of Chapwani island in daylight hours.

It had been suggested that this species had been introduced to Zanzibar, but this male's colour pattern with golden-brown markings on the head and back and grey lips has not been recorded from mainland populations.

properties.descriptio: I literally have no idea where we were at this point. It was on a boat trip with Safari Blue to an island off the coast of Zanzibar... when we saw this coral island with Euphorbia trees intermixed with 'proper' tropical trees. I found it fascinating.

This was on the destination island of the Safari Blue trip... and still I do not know where this island was. Nevertheless, a beautiful Baobab tree awaited us. This was the smaller of the two Baobab trees on the island.
This was at the destination island of our Safari Blue trip. I have no idea where this island was. Shells - embedded in the coral bed of the island.

This photo was taken on the exposed reef of the destination island of our Safari Blue Trip. But I have no idea where this island is. The crab was not skittish. It just sat and wait for me to finish my photos. Also, there was nothing wrong (illness / sick
This was at the launch site of the Safari Blue trip. It was on the Zanzibar - main island. Check out the size of this Cowrie!!
